[{"question":"How do you think things have played out since we last spoke?","answer":"Well, I feel a lot better tonight than I did after South Carolina, Piers.","docId":"120130pmt","qSentId":46,"aSentId":47},{"question":"Was that the kind of Mitt Romney you\u0027ve been looking for?","answer":"Well, I\u0027m a big fan of Mitt Romney, not because of his combativeness, but because of his intellect and his ability to persuade all kinds of people to get together and get the right answers.","docId":"120130pmt","qSentId":51,"aSentId":52},{"question":"But what does that tell you about the way his campaign is now going?","answer":"I think that Newt is going to go all the way to the end, the way he says he\u0027s going to go all the way to the end.","docId":"120130pmt","qSentId":57,"aSentId":58},{"question":"And we\u0027re already seeing him developing into a much more formidable opponent, I would argue, from the debates last week than he may have been if he\u0027d won South Carolina and already won the nomination?","answer":"Look, Mitt Romney\u0027s big issue is connecting, is being comfortable in his own skin, is to let people know who he really is.","docId":"120130pmt","qSentId":73,"aSentId":74},{"question":"That\u0027s the American way, isn\u0027t it?","answer":"Finally, he did it.","docId":"120130pmt","qSentId":115,"aSentId":116},{"question":"It\u0027s all good fodder for the opposition as well, isn\u0027t it?","answer":"Well, look, that\u0027s what\u0027s always said in the primary, Piers.","docId":"120130pmt","qSentId":164,"aSentId":165},{"question":"And Jack, what is the truth about the state of the American economy right now, do you think?","answer":"Well, we have a very tepid recovery, but we do have a recovery.","docId":"120130pmt","qSentId":183,"aSentId":184},{"question":"What about this?","answer":"It\u0027s not all --","docId":"120130pmt","qSentId":236,"aSentId":237},{"question":"So what you\u0027re basically saying, Suzy, is that Mitt Romney\u0027s inability to sing could become an electoral positive for him?","answer":"No.","docId":"120130pmt","qSentId":259,"aSentId":260},{"question":"Why should do you feel that he should pull out?","answer":"Piers, let\u0027s get this straight.","docId":"120130pmt","qSentId":271,"aSentId":272},{"question":"Is it good for the party if Rick Santorum and Ron Paul continue to the bitter end or should one of them take one for the team fairly soon?","answer":"I think it\u0027s good if they end up being strong supporters and believers in whoever the winning candidate is.","docId":"120130pmt","qSentId":281,"aSentId":282},{"question":"How did you come across this extra bit of a tape?","answer":"We felt the same way.","docId":"120130pmt","qSentId":304,"aSentId":305},{"question":"And this actually the box you found the tape in, right?","answer":"This is the box and the tape is in it.","docId":"120130pmt","qSentId":309,"aSentId":310},{"question":"You know, how did we get from A to B?","answer":"Let me go to Douglas Brinkley here.","docId":"120130pmt","qSentId":326,"aSentId":327},{"question":"How significant, do you think, these tapes are in terms of suddenly surfacing like this?","answer":"Well, it\u0027s a fascinating story.","docId":"120130pmt","qSentId":330,"aSentId":331},{"question":"What does that tell you?","answer":"Well, that\u0027s right.","docId":"120130pmt","qSentId":371,"aSentId":372},{"question":"What is the worth, Douglas, would you say, from an historical important point of view?","answer":"Well, you can\u0027t write about the Kennedy assassination without grappling with the contents of this tape, meaning the information that\u0027s now available on it.","docId":"120130pmt","qSentId":413,"aSentId":414},{"question":"How do you know?","answer":"I just saw it on your show.","docId":"120130pmt","qSentId":469,"aSentId":470},{"question":"How do you know he wasn\u0027t told to hide it?","answer":"Because it wouldn\u0027t just be in somebody\u0027s box in their estate.","docId":"120130pmt","qSentId":471,"aSentId":472},{"question":"Do you believe in any conspiracy theories?","answer":"No.","docId":"120130pmt","qSentId":478,"aSentId":479},{"question":"None of them?","answer":"I think it\u0027s fun to do.","docId":"120130pmt","qSentId":480,"aSentId":481},{"question":"Isn\u0027t it, all the Republican race?","answer":"The truth for me is I\u0027m always marketing.","docId":"120130pmt","qSentId":490,"aSentId":491},{"question":"Do you talk about it on your stand-up?","answer":"No.","docId":"120130pmt","qSentId":496,"aSentId":497},{"question":"Wasn\u0027t -- you mean, years ago, they couldn\u0027t say Peter?","answer":"No.","docId":"120130pmt","qSentId":507,"aSentId":508},{"question":"Why is that Peter?","answer":"I don\u0027t know.","docId":"120130pmt","qSentId":510,"aSentId":511},{"question":"Why are you called Howie?","answer":"That\u0027s old English for Ned.","docId":"120130pmt","qSentId":512,"aSentId":513},{"question":"So here is a guy who has one of the world\u0027s most infamous germaphobias, right?","answer":"Yes.","docId":"120130pmt","qSentId":525,"aSentId":526},{"question":"Let me -- can I set the record straight?","answer":"You can try.","docId":"120130pmt","qSentId":548,"aSentId":549},{"question":"Do you know who he is?","answer":"I don\u0027t.","docId":"120130pmt","qSentId":551,"aSentId":552},{"question":"He wouldn\u0027t get past first go, would he?","answer":"But it\u0027s great television because it\u0027s awkward and uncomfortable.","docId":"120130pmt","qSentId":597,"aSentId":598},{"question":"How are you feeling about Howard Stern replacing me?","answer":"You know what, I\u0027ll be totally honest, I loved working with you much more than you loved working with me.","docId":"120130pmt","qSentId":609,"aSentId":610},{"question":"Would you like him to?","answer":"No, I don\u0027t think that\u0027s our job.","docId":"120130pmt","qSentId":618,"aSentId":619},{"question":"How many followers do you have?","answer":"I don\u0027t have a lot of followers, because I can\u0027t plug -- @HowieMMandel.","docId":"120130pmt","qSentId":627,"aSentId":628},{"question":"Why would anybody want to follow you?","answer":"Because I\u0027m wonderfully entertaining.","docId":"120130pmt","qSentId":633,"aSentId":634},{"question":"Who told you about twitter?","answer":"You told me to do it.","docId":"120130pmt","qSentId":636,"aSentId":637},{"question":"Is that why you called me here today?","answer":"I would like you to apologize.","docId":"120130pmt","qSentId":652,"aSentId":653},{"question":"For being me?","answer":"Say sorry for being so annoying.","docId":"120130pmt","qSentId":654,"aSentId":655},{"question":"But what happens to the 30 million people without jobs?","answer":"We have to -- and this is -- I don\u0027t know.","docId":"120130pmt","qSentId":723,"aSentId":724},{"question":"Really?","answer":"You can do serious.","docId":"120130pmt","qSentId":732,"aSentId":733}]